{{rfv-etymology|lang=en}}
From a variation of {{term|yea|lang=en}}, itself from {{etyl|enm|en}} {{term|ya|lang=enm}}, {{term|ye|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term/t|ang|ġēa||yes}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{term/t|gem-pro|*ja||yes; thus, so}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{term/t|ine-pro|*yē||already}}. Cognate with Dutch {{term|ja|lang=nl}}, German {{term|ja|lang=de}}, Danish {{term|ja|lang=da}}, Bokmål {{term|ja|lang=nb}}, New Norwegian {{term|ja|lang=nn}} and Swedish {{term|ja|lang=sv}}.

Alternative etymology derives ''yeah'' from a drawling pronunciation of {{term|yes|lang=en}}. For further etymology, see {{l|en|yes}}.

